extends layout.pug

block content 
  article.grid-container.portfolio-intro
    div

      //- Add a title or heading like My Portfolio, or Hey, Potential Employers, or Let's make the web great together! 
      h1 My JavaScript Portfolio

      //- Add a description for your portfolio, what this project is, its purpose, what it's supposed to accomplish, etc. 
      p.lead.text-light
        | This is a portfolio of the JavaScript projects I've completed
        | as part of the #[a(href="https://teamtreehouse.com") Treehouse] Full Stack JavaScript Techdegree program.
        | The page you're looking at now is the sixth project, and is the first server-side project, 
        | utilizing Node.js, Express and Pug.
  article.grid-container.portfolio-index
    
    .grid-x.grid-margin-x.small-up-2.medium-up-2.large-up-3

      //- Use the Pug `each` iterator to create a project img, title and link 
      //- in the markup for each of the projects you are showcasing.  
      each project in projects
        //- Use a combination of interpolation and template literals as needed to dynamically 
        //- generate the routes in the href, as well as the img's src and the projects title.
        
        //- Here's what the Pug for each project example should look like. 

        .cell
          a(href=`projects/${project.id}`)
            img.thumbnail(src=`${project.image_urls[0]}`)
            h5= project.project_name
      
